# IMS (Inventory Management System)


## What this repository contains
- Docker Compose stack running Laravel (PHP-FPM) + Nginx + PostgreSQL + MongoDB + Redis + Node (for React dev)
- A React frontend scaffold that calls Laravel API endpoints
- Laravel CRUD for inventory items (model, migration, controller, API routes)


## Quick start (Windows with Docker Desktop + Git Bash)
1. Clone repository (or create project folder and paste files)
2. Open Git Bash and `cd` into the project root
3. Create folders: `backend`, `frontend`, `nginx/conf.d`
4. Paste the files from this repo into the correct locations


Create Laravel and React apps using Docker (if you do not have Composer/Node locally):


```bash
# from ims-project
# create Laravel in backend
docker run --rm -v ${PWD}/backend:/var/www -w /var/www composer:2 create-project laravel/laravel .


# create React app in frontend
docker run --rm -v ${PWD}/frontend:/usr/src/app -w /usr/src/app node:18 npx create-react-app .